main event: A sighting of a saucer-shaped object with yellow-green lights that hovered and moved erratically over Frankfort, Kentucky on January 17-18, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 1.3 hours, and it clearly pulsated, changing colors between red, yellow, and green.
The witnesses believed the object was not an aircraft and that its movements, which included going up and down and side to side, were unusual.
There was a power failure in the area on January 16, 1967, the day before the sighting.
The description is consistent with an astronomical event, but the witnesses were certain it was not an aircraft.
Similar sightings of strange lights were reported in the area around the same time.
